2. Maximum Number of Rainbows
Problem Statement
A rainbow is formed using seven distinct colours: Violet (v), Indigo (i), Blue (b), Green (g),
Yellow (y), Orange (o), and Red (r).
Each rainbow requires exactly one occurrence of each colour.
You are given a string S consisting of lowercase characters, where each character
represents the first letter of a colour.
Your task is to determine the maximum number of complete rainbows that can be formed
using the characters of the string. Each character can be used only once.

Input Format
 A single string S containing lowercase alphabets.

Output Format
 Print an integer representing the maximum number of rainbows that can be
formed.

Sample Input
vbgybro
Sample Output
1

// Java code 

import java.util.*;
public class Main {
public static void main(String[] args) {
    Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
    String s =sc.next();
    int[] count = new int[7];
    for(char c : s.toCharArray()) {
        if(c == 'v')
           count[0]++;
        else if(c == 'i')
           count[1]++;
        else if(c == 'b')
           count[2]++;
        else if(c == 'g')
            count[3]++;
        else if(c == 'y')
            count[4]++;
        else if(c == 'o')
            count[5]++;
        else if(c == 'r')
            count[6]++;
      }
      int min = Integr.MAX_VALUE;
      for(int i=0; i<7; i++) {
          int min = (min, count[i]);
      }
      System.out.println(min);
      sc.close();
  }
}
